HAPPY NEW YEAR LEGENDS! 🥳 Oliebollen Ingredients - 14g dried yeast - 125ml warm water - 60g caster sugar - 450g flour - Pinch salt - 250ml milk - 2 eggs - 100g currants - 100g raisins - 1 granny smith apple, diced - Icing sugar for dusting - Oil for frying (I use peanut) Method 1. Place the yeast into the warm water, stir and set aside. 2. In a large mixing bowl add the sugar, flour, and salt and mix. 3. Create a well in the centre and add the milk, beaten eggs and water yeast mixture. 4. Starting from the centre and working your way out mix the batter. 5. Mix through the currants, raisins and apple. 6. Leave the mixed dough in a bowl big enough for it to double, cover it with plastic wrap and set aside for 1 hour. 7. In a large pot 2/3 full with oil, heat until it reaches 160c. 8. Using 2 spoons, place in golf ball size pieces of the dough in batches of 5-6 and cook until golden brown - around 5-6 minutes. 9. Remove from the oil and leave on a wire rack to drain. 10. Dust HEAVY with icing sugar and enjoy!

freezer-friendly sunday meal prep rundown!!! 🤝🥶 everything I made: - english muffin breakfast sandwiches (recipe below) - cilantro lime chicken (recipe on my 10/22 meal prep IGhighlight) - pumpkin chili (recipe on my 10/22 meal prep IGhighlight) - chicken & cauli rice burrito bowls (recipe below) everything was stocked in my freezer waiting for me when i got back from my trip 👏🫶 for the breakfast sandwiches, blend 10 eggs, 2 cups cottage cheese, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp black pepper, & 1/2 tsp garlic powder in a blender on high speed. preheat oven to 300 and grease a baking dish with oil. pour in the egg mixture, add 4 cups chopped spinach and incorporate, and bake for 30-40 minutes or until fully cooked (will depend on size of baking dish). slice into even squares when fully cooled, then assemble the sandwiches by taking a sliced english muffin and adding the egg, then shredded cheddar cheese on top. wrap in parchment paper and store in a bag in the freezer. for the burrito bowl filling, heat 2 tbsp oil in a large skillet over medium heat, then add 1 lb ground chicken and almost fully cook it, stirring occasionally. add in 1 lb frozen cauliflower rice and fully defrost while the chicken finishes cooking. add in 1 packet of taco seasoning + 1/3 cup water and bring to a simmer. mix in 1/2 lb frozen bell peppers and sauté until tender, then remove from heat and store. let me know any Qs in the comments!! 💕

BIG MAC SALAD JARS Ingredients: 1 lb lean ground meat, I used chicken but you can use beef or turkey! 1 head iceberg lettuce, chopped 1/2 cup diced white onion 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, halved 1/2 cup dill pickle slices 1/2 cup fat free shredded cheddar cheese 1 tsp garlic powder 1/2 tsp onion powder 1/2 tsp paprika 1/2 tsp chili powder 1 tsp salt Big Mac sauce 1/2 cup fat free plain Greek yogurt 3 tbsp sugar free ketchup 1 tbsp mustard 3 tbsp dill relish 1 tbsp white vinegar 1 tsp garlic powder 1 tsp onion powder 1/2 tsp paprika 1 tsp salt Instructions 1. Place a pan over medium heat and spray with nonstick cooking spray. Add ground meat and season with garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, chili powder, and salt. Cook until fully cooked through, crumbling the meat as you go. 2. While meat cooks chop your veggies and whisk together all Big Mac sauce ingredients in a bowl until smooth. Set aside. 3. Grab 3-4 glas jars (I used 3 32 oz glass jars, but if you have smaller jars you can make 4), layer Big Mac sauce, meat, onion, tomatoes, pickles, cheese, and lastly, lettuce. Store in the fridge for up to 4 days.

you all loved these high protein breakfast biscuits & honestly SAME so I've been experimenting with different flavors 🫶 easy to make, only one bowl required, & you can freeze and reheat them!! the recipe makes 12 biscuits and l've found a few mins in the airfryer is perfect for reheating, but a microwave or oven works too!! here's everything you need: * 1 tbsp avocado or olive oil * 1 small yellow onion, diced * 16oz ground pork (or ground chicken/turkey) * 1 + 1/2 cups almond flour * 1/2 cup coconut flour * 1 tsp salt * 1/2 tsp black pepper * 2 tsp oregano * 1 tsp garlic powder * 2 tsp baking powder * 6 eggs, beaten * 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese * 1 cup chopped roasted red peppers * 4oz goat cheese preheat oven to 400 and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. start by heating the oil in a skillet over medium heat, then adding the onion and sauteing for 5 minutes. clear the center of the pan and add in the ground pork. let cook, stirring constantly, until the pork is completely browned, about 10 minutes. set aside. whisk together the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl, then mix in the beaten eggs, cheddar cheese, pork mixture, and roasted red peppers. use a spatula to fully incorporate. use a large cookie scoop or spoon to make 12 evenly sized balls of mix and place them on the sheet pan. rub a little bit of oil in your hands and then shape them into a biscuit shape by pressing down. place in the oven for 8-10 minutes, until firm and browning on the outside, then remove and create a crater in the center of each one (where the goat cheese will go). add about a tablespoon of goat cheese to each biscuit. place back in the oven for 4-6 minutes to finish baking. remove from the oven and let cool completely before storing in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 4 days or freezer for a month. enjoy!

Here’s how I made mine: 1. Take the burrata out of the container and place in a bowl. Add warm water to the bowl and let sit for at least 10 mins 2. In a small bowl, combine 4tbsp olive oil, 1 tbsp chili oil, 1tsp bread dipping seasonings (of your choice), and 1/2 tsp balsamic vinegar 3. Place the burrata in a serving bowl and drizzle the oil mixture over it 4. Cut the burrata open and let the creamy goodness combine with the oil 5. Serve with fresh bread!

HIDDEN VEGGIE PROTEIN ALFREDO Nutrition for just the sauce (makes around 6 servings) Per serving: 120 kcal 4g fat 6g carbs 15g protein Ingredients 1 box of pasta of choice 2 cups cauliflower florets 1 1/4 cups low fat cottage cheese 2/3 cup Parmigiano Reggiano cheese 3 tsp minced garlic 1 tsp onion powder 1 tsp dried rosemary 2 tsp salt Pepper to taste 1 1/4 cups milk of choice (I used @fairlife low fat milk) Instructions 1. Cook pasta according to package instructions. 2. While pasta cooks bring another large pot of water to a boil and add your cauliflower florets. Boil until they are soft and break apart with a fork. Drain and let cool. 3. To a blender add cottage cheese, parm cheese, garlic, onion powder, rosemary, salt, pepper, almond milk, and cauliflower. Blend on high until smooth and creamy. Add more salt and pepper if needed. 4. Add pasta and sauce back to the pasta pot and mix together until well combined (you will have sauce leftover). Store any leftover sauce in an airtight container in the fridge.

Brussels sprouts, shredded kale and almond salad Ingredients: - 6 shallots, thinly sliced - 100g (about 3.5 oz) flaked almonds - 6 tbsp (3 fl oz) olive oil - 500g (about 1.1 lbs) Brussels sprouts, sliced very thin - ½ bunch kale, finely sliced - 2 tbsp miso - juice of 1 lemon - salt, to taste Method: 1. In a large frying pan over medium heat, toast the almonds. Once toasted, remove them from the pan and set aside. 2. In the same pan, add 2 tablespoons of olive oil and sauté the shallots with a pinch of salt until they are soft and fragrant and have some colour. 3. Place the thinly sliced Brussels sprouts and kale in ice water to wash well, then drain thoroughly. 4. To make the dressing, combine 4 tablespoons of olive oil, miso, lemon juice, and a pinch of salt in a jar. Shake well to blend the ingredients. 5. In a large bowl, add the drained Brussels sprouts, kale, half of the almonds, half of the shallots, and the dressing. Toss everything together until well mixed. 6. Serve the salad and garnish with the remaining almonds and shallots.
